17/05/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- EUFOR is not insisting on resignations in relation to the recent incidents at the Republika Srpska Army oath-taking ceremonies, EUFOR spokesman Frank Cockburn said Monday (16 May). 
However, he emphasised that domestic authorities are responsible for tackling the problem. 
During a meeting at the weekend, EUFOR Commander Major General David Leakey and NATO HQ Commander General Steven P. 
Schook requested that the BiH presidency take action to identify the responsible individuals and prevent the repetition of such incidents. 
NATO HQ spokesman Derek Chappell said action was expected by 24 May. 
(RTRS, NTV Hayat - 16/05/05)
